### 1.2. Elevator pitch {#1.2.-elevator-pitch}

Die Trying is a fast-paced, highly strategic, card game where the goal is to accumulate the   
most wealth before you kick the bucket. It’s a PvP class based game where you get to choose between a knight, mage, or thief and have to decide when to use your abilities to gain the upper hand against your competitors. The winner is whoever makes the most money, not the last man standing.

## 2\. Game Overview {#2.-game-overview}

### 2.1. Game concept {#2.1.-game-concept}

Card drawing game where each draw is filled with tension, will you gain more gold or draw a trap and take damage. Surviving longer means you will have more opportunities to make money, but while the deck shrinks, it becomes more likely for you to draw a trap. The deck is primarily filled with gold and traps, with some potions and treasures along the way.

### 2.2. Audience {#2.2.-audience}

Die Trying is designed for people between their early teens to early 40s. It’s designed to be casual and quick, making it fun for new players and more competitive for tabletop gamers. Decisionmaking is key as there are only a few major decisions to be made. The games last about 10 minutes

### 2.3. Genre {#2.3.-genre}

Card game / Strategy with survival elements

### 2.4. Setting {#2.4.-setting}

The setting is a fantasy world where mages, dungeons, and potions appear. The world is meant to be loose and comedic to contribute to its fast paced nature.

### 2.5. Player {#2.5.-player}

3 or more players. Each play as either mage, knight or thief and have different resources allocated to them through gameplay. The knight has shields, mage has mana, and the thief has dodging abilities. Each class is played differently, but is kept simple enough to pick up quickly.

